    h1 Chips
    .docs-index
    p Chips (Tags) represent complex entities in small blocks, such as a contact. They can contain a photo, short title string, and brief information.
    h2 Chips Layout
    p Let's look at basic chip HTML layout
    pre
      code.html
        | &lt;div class="chip"&gt;
        |     &lt;div class="chip-media"&gt;
        |         &lt;img src="http://lorempixel.com/100/100/people/9/"&gt;
        |     &lt;/div&gt;
        |     &lt;div class="chip-label"&gt;Jane Doe&lt;/div&gt;
        |     &lt;a href="#" class="chip-delete"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
        | &lt;/div&gt;
    p Where
    ul
      li
        p <code>&lt;div class="chip"&gt;</code> - Chip container
        ul
          li
            p <code>&lt;div class="chip-media"&gt;</code> - Chip "media" element, can contain image/avatar or icon. <em>Optional</em>
          li
            p <code>&lt;div class="card-label"&gt;</code> - Chip text label
          li
            p <code>&lt;a class="card-delete"&gt;</code> - Chip delete icon-link. <em>Optional</em>
